= Conversion Tools

These tools help you avoid the most common beginner mistake: confusing polite interest with real demand.

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.4pt)[#emph[The 10-Message Test]
#v(3pt)
Send 10 direct, personal messages before judging an idea. Don’t count likes, compliments, or vague interest. Count replies that show pain or willingness to act.

#emph[Notes]
#v(3pt)
#line(length: 100%)
#line(length: 100%)
#line(length: 100%)

]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.4pt)[#emph[The \$10 Tiny Offer Test]
#v(3pt)
Turn your idea into one small thing someone could buy for around \$10. If nobody wants the tiny version, don’t build the big version yet.

#emph[Notes]
#v(3pt)
#line(length: 100%)
